{"id":"astro-ph/0208259","submitter":"Jozef Klacka","authors":"Jozef Klacka","title":"On Radiation Pressure and the Poynting-Robertson Effect for Fluffy Dust\n  Particles","comments":null,"journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"astro-ph","license":null,"abstract":"  Equation of motion for real dust particle under the action of electromagnetic\nradiation is more general than equation of motion corresponding to standardly\nused Poynting-Robertson effect (P-R effect). As a consequence, orbital\nevolution of particles may significantly differ from that corresponding to the\nP-R effect. The paper discusses recently published (Icarus, June 2002)\nderivation of equation of motion, which is in contradiction with known\nrelativistically covariant formulation. The ``new'' derivation does not respect\nfundamental physical laws (law of conservation of energy, law of conservation\nof momentum) which must hold in any frame of reference. Application of the\nderived ``general'' equation of motion to the special case treated by Einstein\nin 1905 yields result which is not consistent with Einstein's result. Correct\nsolution is presented.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 13 Aug 2002 19:19:31 GMT"}],"update_date":"2007-05-23"}
